TAB to move around, Arrows to adjust values.	按 TAB 移動，方向鍵調整數值。
Choose a new character type?	要選擇新的角色類型嗎？
Please choose a longer name for your character.	請為您的角色選擇較長的名稱。
With the help of the Slave Woman, Mayzun, you found the Emir Ali hiding in his bedroom.  With your urging (and a few sharp remarks from Mayzun), the Emir swore he'd restore the city.  By the first light of dawn, the Emir Ali al-Din Hasan ordered all fighting to cease and proclaimed the evil rule of Ad Avis and Khaveen to be over.  As the Emir began an incredibly dull speech, you slipped away to complete your quest.	在女奴梅尊的協助下，你在臥室裡找到了藏身的埃米爾阿里。在你的勸說（以及梅尊幾句尖銳的提醒）下，埃米爾發誓要恢復這座城市。天色微亮之際，埃米爾阿里·阿丁·哈桑下令停止一切戰鬥，並宣告阿德·阿維斯與哈維因的邪惡統治就此終結。就在埃米爾開始發表冗長乏味的演說時，你悄悄溜走，繼續完成你的任務。
You stare in wonder at the powerful transformation of the Plaza by the magic of the Water Elemental.	你驚訝地凝視著水元素的魔法為廣場帶來的驚人蛻變。
Will anyone speak for this Stranger from the North?	有誰願意為這位來自北方的異鄉人發言？
We are Shameen and Shema, keepers of the Katta's Tail Inn.  When the Katta were driven from Raseir, we journeyed to the Northland in search of a hero.	我們是沙明與舍瑪，卡塔之尾旅店的主人。當卡塔族被逐出拉希爾時，我們啟程前往北方尋找英雄。
He journeyed back with us to Shapeir.  Here he defeated the Elementals of Fire, Air, Earth, and Water to save our city.	他與我們一同回到夏皮爾。在此，他擊敗了火、風、土、水四大元素，拯救了我們的城市。
Who will speak for this man of compassion?	有誰願意為這位仁慈之人發言？
Who will speak for this man of Honor?	有誰願意為這位榮譽之人發言？
I am Zayishah, daughter of the Emir Ali Al-Din Hasan.	我是扎伊莎，埃米爾阿里·阿丁·哈桑之女。
Gronk.	咕嚕。
I am the Poet Omar, Teller of tales for all to hear.	我是詩人歐瑪爾，向眾人講述故事的說書人。
I proclaim this man a Hero,	我在此宣告，此人為英雄，
Honesty in dealing with others, and Mercy to his enemies.	待人誠實，對敵仁慈。
He is a man of great Honor.	他是一位極具榮譽感的人。
I, Rasha Rakeesh SahTarna,	我，拉沙·拉基什·薩塔納，
You are now a Paladin.	你現在是一位聖騎士了。
a:glory2.sav	a:glory2.sav
CONGRATULATIONS!! You have successfully completed "Quest for Glory II:  Trial by Fire" with the maximum possible score, %d of %d!! We welcome you to the ranks of the few, the proud, the True Heroes!	恭喜！！你已成功以滿分通關《英雄傳奇 II：烈火試煉》，%d 分（滿分 %d）！！歡迎加入真英雄──這群為數不多、令人驕傲的行列！
Congratulations!  You have successfully completed "Quest for Glory II:  Trial by Fire." Your final score was %d of %d possible Puzzle Points.	恭喜！你已成功通關《英雄傳奇 II：烈火試煉》。你的最終得分為 %d 分（滿分 %d 解謎點數）。
If you have not already done so, we encourage you to play "Quest for Glory II" again with the other two character types; many of the puzzles are different, or have alternate solutions.	如果你還沒試過，建議你用另外兩種角色類型再玩一次《英雄傳奇 II》；許多謎題會有所不同，或有其他解法。
In the meantime, you are already a winner! Please insert a writable disk in your floppy drive to save your winning Hero for use in "Quest for Glory III:  Shadows of Darkness."	不論如何，你已經是勝利者！請在軟碟機中插入可寫入的磁碟片，儲存你的過關英雄，以便在《英雄傳奇 III：暗影之詛》中使用。
File already exists.  Do you wish to overwrite?	檔案已存在，要覆寫嗎？
The save character file has been created.  Save this disk for use with "Quest for Glory III:  Shadows of Darkness" from Sierra On-Line.	角色存檔已建立完成。請保留此磁碟片，以便用於 Sierra On-Line 的《英雄傳奇 III：暗影之詛》。
Do you wish to try saving your character again?	要再試一次儲存角色嗎？
Thank you for playing "Quest for Glory II:  Trial by Fire," and congratulations again on winning.  We'll see you again soon in "Quest for Glory III: Shadows of Darkness."	感謝您遊玩《英雄傳奇 II：烈火試煉》，再次恭喜您獲勝。我們將在《英雄傳奇 III：暗影之詛》中再會。
    Congratulations, Paladin!  [score %d of %d]	    恭喜你，聖騎士！  [得分 %d，滿分 %d]
       Hero of Two Lands!  [score %d of %d]	       兩地英雄！  [得分 %d，滿分 %d]
Ha Ha Ha Haaaaaaah Ha Haah Ha Ha Haaaah Ha Haaaa!	哈哈哈哈哈哈哈！哈哈哈！哈哈哈哈哈！哈哈哈哈！
And so, as the moon moves slowly through the starry sky above the mountains and the desert of Shapeir, our Hero bids a fond "Adieu" to his latest set of adventures and miserable puns.  Where will the road lead next...?	就這樣，當月亮緩緩劃過夏皮爾山巒與沙漠上空的星空，我們的英雄向他這趟充滿冒險與蹩腳雙關語的旅程道一聲珍重的「再見」。前方的道路，又將通往何方呢……？
But wait!  There's more to come in the next thrilling saga of "Quest for Glory" by Lori and Corey.	且慢！柯瑞與蘿莉·柯爾打造的《英雄傳奇》系列，還有更多精彩故事等著你！
Our next game...	我們的下一部作品……
Twinkle, twinkle.	閃爍，閃爍。
The best way to get goods across the desert is by pack saurus.	要橫越沙漠運送貨物，最好的方法就是使用馱獸索魯斯。
The Bedouins of the desert are good people, for the most part.	沙漠中的貝都因人大多是善良的人。
Before the sun has risen over the mountaintops, you are awakened by Shameen, who tells you that even now, the caravan to Raseir is preparing to depart.	天還未亮，太陽尚未升上山頭，沙明便將你喚醒，告訴你前往拉希爾的商隊此刻正準備出發。
Shema greets you as you leave the room with some breakfast and supplies to take with you.  The inn is filled with katta merchants who wish you luck upon your departure.	你離開房間時，舍瑪迎上前來，遞給你早餐與隨行補給。旅店裡擠滿了卡塔族商人，紛紛祝你一路順風。
As you pass through the gate of Shapeir, the gate guard presents you with a new saurus, a gift from the Sultan.  Ahead in the desert sands awaits a mass of Saurii and riders being led by the Caravan Master, a huge Centaur who orders the Caravan into motion before the sun can be seen.	當你穿過夏皮爾城門時，守衛送上蘇丹贈予的一頭新索魯斯。前方沙地上，一大群索魯斯與騎手正等候著，由商隊隊長率領──那是一位魁梧的半人馬，他在日出前便下令商隊啟程。
The only way of getting goods across the desert is by pack saurus.	橫越沙漠運送貨物的唯一方法，就是使用馱獸索魯斯。
The caravan comes under siege from hundreds of nomadic brigands.  Your small group is vastly outnumbered.  The situation looks grim.	商隊遭到數百名遊牧盜匪的圍攻。你們人數懸殊、寡不敵眾，情勢看來十分嚴峻。
I love the smell of victory in the morning.      ......  It smells like.....sweat.. no, no      ...oregano ....nooo...like Victory!  Yea      Victory!...Yea! Yea!  That's the ticket.	我愛清晨勝利的氣味。      ......  聞起來像是.....汗水..不對，不對      ...牛至草....不對不對...像是勝利！耶      勝利！...耶！耶！就是這樣！
After a week of travelling, you leave the Caravan when it comes within sight of the city of Raseir.	經過一週的跋涉，當商隊終於望見拉希爾城時，你便與商隊分道揚鑣。
He rears up and salutes you, and you watch the Caravan move onward into the desert.	牠人立起身向你致意，你目送商隊繼續深入沙漠。
The saurus is an amazing beast.  This steed must have remained at the gate, awaiting your future need, while you carried on your business in Raseir.	索魯斯真是令人驚嘆的坐騎。想必在你於拉希爾辦事期間，牠便一直留在城門邊，等候你未來的需要。
